<h3>Project Hummingbird</h3>
<h4>Project Manager: Howard Yang</h4>

<p>Project Hummingbird is Student Space Systems’ first actively controlled aerial vehicle. Hummingbird is a custom designed and built quadcopter that is being built as a platform for SSS to experiment with control theory techniques. The quadrotor form-factor was chosen because as opposed to a launch vehicle, flights are safer, It it controlled by an Arduino Uno, which uses a GPS receiver, barometric altimeter, and 9-DOF inertial measurement unit to estimate its state and determine what speed to run each of the four motors at.</p>

